{{Italic title|force=yes}} {{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Social, Political, and Economic Studies | image = <!-- or |cover= --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | former_name = Journal of Social and Political Studies | abbreviation = J. Soc. Political Econ. Stud. | bluebook = <!-- For law journals only --> | discipline = [[Economics]], [[political science]], [[sociology]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English | editor = [[Roger Pearson (anthropologist)|Roger Pearson]] | publisher = [[Scott-Townsend Publishers]] | country = | history = 1976-present | frequency = Quarterly | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 0278-839X | eISSN = | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = 82644115 | OCLC = 691862682 | website = http://jspes.org | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }} The '''''Journal of Social, Political, and Economic Studies''''' ({{ISSN|0278-839X}}) is a quarterly journal published by [[Scott-Townsend Publishers]], the publishing arm of the Council for Social and Economic Studies. It was founded in 1976 by anthropologist [[Roger Pearson (anthropologist)|Roger Pearson]], and was originally published by his [[Council for American Affairs]], an American representative in the [[World Anti Communist League]]. It is now published by the Council for Social and Economic Studies, of which Pearson was the president as of 1982.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Winston|first=Andrew S.|title=The Context of Correctness: A Comment on Rushton|journal=Journal of Social Distress and the Homeless|publisher=Human Sciences Press|volume= 5|issue= 2 |year=1996|pages=231–250|url=http://www.psychology.uoguelph.ca/faculty/winston/papers/rushton.html|accessdate=2008-12-10|doi=10.1007/BF02088001}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OBsHSzmkYHkC&pg=PA257&dq=%22Journal+of+Social,+Political,+and+Economic+Studies%22+right-wing&hl=en&ei=JWWlTtiHLaTa0QHQwr2RBQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CEcQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=The Science and Politics of Racial ... - William H. Tucker - Google Books |publisher=Books.google.com |date= |accessdate=2011-12-23}}</ref> It has been identified as one of two international journals which regularly publishes articles pertaining to [[race and intelligence]] with the goal of supporting the idea that [[white people]] are inherently superior (the other such journal being ''[[Mankind Quarterly]]'').<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CruyXMRn7X4C |title=Pioneer on Indigenous Rights |last=Stavenhagen |first=Rodolfo |date=2012-12-14 |publisher=Springer Science & Business Media |isbn=9783642341502 |pages=90 |language=en}}</ref> Notable contributors to the journal include [[Jack Kemp]] and [[Jesse Helms]].<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=f2N-PNp5_HQC |title=A Curriculum of Repression: A Pedagogy of Racial History in the United States |last=Kharem |first=Haroon |date=2006 |publisher=Peter Lang |isbn=9780820456638 |pages=133 |language=en}}</ref> In 1982, U.S. President [[Ronald Reagan]] wrote a letter to Pearson personally thanking him for the most recent issue of the Journal, which was never disavowed by the White House. The White House did, however, request that Pearson stop using the letter.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZWAHmLuZeIoC |title=Old Nazis, the New Right, and the Republican Party |last=Bellant |first=Russ |date=1991 |publisher=South End Press |isbn=9780896084186 |pages=60-62 |language=en}}</ref>
