{{Infobox diagnostic | name = Simple clinical colitis activity index | image = | alt = | caption = | pronounce = | synonyms = | purpose = Determining severity of [[ulcerative colitis]] | reference_range = | calculator = | DiseasesDB = <!--{{DiseasesDB2|numeric_id}}--> | ICD10 = <!--{{ICD10|Group|Major|minor|LinkGroup|LinkMajor}} or {{ICD10PCS|code|char1/char2/char3/char4}}--> | ICD9 = | ICDO = | MedlinePlus = <!--article_number--> | eMedicine = <!--article_number--> | MeshID = | OPS301 = <!--{{OPS301|code}}--> | LOINC = <!--{{LOINC|code}}--> }} The '''Simple Clinical Colitis Activity Index''' ('''SCCAI''') is a diagnostic tool and questionnaire used to assess the severity of [[symptoms]] in people who have from [[ulcerative colitis]]. It was created in 1998 and is still used to assess the severity of symptoms.<ref name="WalmsleyAyres1998">{{cite journal|last1=Walmsley|first1=R S|last2=Ayres|first2=R C S|last3=Pounder|first3=R E|last4=Allan|first4=R N|title=A simple clinical colitis activity index|journal=Gut|volume=43|issue=1|year=1998|pages=29–32|issn=0017-5749|doi=10.1136/gut.43.1.29|url=http://gut.bmj.com/content/48/suppl_1/A1.extract|pmc=1727189}}</ref><!-- please retain this historical, non-MEDRS citation --> It is also used for research purposes to determine the efficacy of various treatments aimed at relieving symptoms.<ref name="MardiniGrigorian2014">{{cite journal|last1=Mardini|first1=Houssam E.|last2=Grigorian|first2=Alla Y.|title=Probiotic Mix VSL#3 Is Effective Adjunctive Therapy for Mild to Moderately Active Ulcerative Colitis|journal=Inflammatory Bowel Diseases|volume=20|issue=9|year=2014|pages=1562–1567|issn=1078-0998|doi=10.1097/MIB.0000000000000084|postscript=; Access provided by the University of Pittsburgh|pmid=24918321}}</ref> The calculated score ranges from 0 to 19, where active disease is a score of 5 or higher.
The score is determined by asking the person with colitis questions regarding:
* [[Defecation|Bowel frequency]] at day/night * Urgency of defecation * [[Blood in stool]] * General health * Extracolonic manifestations
